# Detecting Collisions

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UN2rAjJ-Za8?list=PL5d-IZ0FwWaH8lcsqn0tuYq5E7j_yJb7M" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen class="lefted"></iframe>

Interaction is an important part of many models. Whether you are modeling a predator/prey relationship, or a reproducing ecosystem, collision detection allows for more biological realism.

Collision blocks are located in the "Detection" drawer, along with the blocks that you can use for proximity direction.  For more information on using collisions, watch the attached video, located at https://youtu.be/UN2rAjJ-Za8.


